The paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques, specifically ML/DL classification models, to aid human decisions in determining Medicaid eligibility. This suggests that the paper falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a method to improve the fairness of regressive classifiers, which could fall under the categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper also discusses experiments conducted on a dataset, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
